Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Zinc Sulfate Market

The zinc sulfate market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 7.50% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 2,853.564 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on zinc sulfate market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in the demand of applications of raw material for manufacturing latex products, pigment lithopone, desulphurization process is escalating the growth of the zinc sulfate market.

Zinc sulfate can be referred to as an inorganic compound identified by the formula ZnSO4. It is an odourless, colourless, and crystalline solid. Originally, it was identified as white vitriol. It is easily soluble in the water with its aqueous solution, being acidic and slightly soluble in ethanol and glycerol. It has non-flammable, non-oxidizing, and non-combustible properties.

Major factors that are expected to boost the growth of the zinc sulfate market in the forecast period are the rise in the production of agrochemicals. Furthermore, the increase in zinc deficiency disorders is further anticipated to propel the growth of the zinc sulfate market. Moreover, the development in the agriculture and agrochemicals industries is further estimated to cushion the growth of the zinc sulfate market. On the other hand, insufficient health alertness, minimal dietary intake, less bioavailability, and unhygienic circumstances are a few of the factors that are projected to impede the growth of the zinc sulfate market in the timeline period.

In addition, the rise in the economies of scale, agglomeration, and density will further provide potential opportunities for the growth of the zinc sulfate market in the coming years. However, the unbalanced political situation and improper priority setting in the national agenda might further challenge the growth of the zinc sulfate market in the near future.

